smallsrv (3.05.71a) unstable; urgency=low

  * Updated format for IP-country database.
  * Little changes in Proxy,HTTP,SMTP, Statistics.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Sun, 24 Jun 2007 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.05.69) unstable; urgency=low

  * New antispam features has been added to SMTP server. "Graylist" --
    it is common or user's personal file like "goodlist" and "badlist",
    may content, e-mails, IPs adresses, regular expresion paterns etc. If
    any of condition from common or personal "graylist" will true, server
    will not receive message immidiatle, for a time or until IP will not
    checked. This will well work with fake e-mail address. The message
    will be receive after little time if sender don't try to send
    something to fake address.
  * Little changes in ISAPI. Php5isapi.dll must work as PHP
    interpreter.
  * FTP and Proxy limits has been corrected.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Sun, 10 Jun 2007 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.05.68) unstable; urgency=low

  * Now in options for web root directories you may direct a URL link
    to another web server.
   - In this case when resource will be required the server will work
     like proxy.
  * Proxy has been updated
  * DNS has been updated.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Mon, 08 Oct 2007 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.05.72a) unstable; urgency=low

  * IPv6 for HTTP corrected
  * Little changes in SMTP.
  * Advanced protection for one type of DoS has been added.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Sun, 05 Aug 2007 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.05.71a) unstable; urgency=low

  * Updated format for IP-country database.
  * Little changes in Proxy,HTTP,SMTP, Statistics.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Sun, 24 Jun 2007 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.05.69) unstable; urgency=low

  * New antispam features has been added to SMTP server. "graylist" --
    it is common or user's personal file like "goodlist" and "badlist",
    may content, e-mails, IPs adresses, regular expresion paterns etc. If
    any of condition from common or personal "graylist" will true, server
    will not receive message immidiatle, for a time or until IP will not
    checked. This will well work with fake e-mail address. The message
    will be receive after little time if sender don't try to send
    something to fake address.
  * Little changes in ISAPI. Php5isapi.dll must work as PHP
    interpreter.
  * FTP and Proxy limits has been corrected.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Sun, 10 Jun 2007 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.05.68) unstable; urgency=low

  * Now in options for web root directories you may direct a URL link
    to another web server. In this case when resource will be required
    the server will work like proxy.
  * Proxy has been updated
  * DNS has been updated.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Mon, 30 Apr 2007 00:00:00 +0300

