smallsrv (3.05.40) unstable; urgency=low

  * Little changes

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Sat, 28 Jan 2006 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.05.39) unstable; urgency=low

  * IPv6 support has been added.
    - May be check on optionaly.
    - Now through IPv6 may work HTTP,POP3,SMTP income, Proxy income,
      DNS request about us domain
    - SMTP server still send messages outside through IPv4, DNS still
      send recurcive requests to resolve names through IPv4.
    - If you use buildin DNS for caching/resolving then unrecomendet to
      enable IPv6 for DNS.
  * Now DNS support AAAA record.
  * Little changes in SMTP.
  * Little changes in DNS.
  * An error has been found and fixed in proxy.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Sun, 08 Jan 2006 00:00:00 +0300

