 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Mon, 12 Nov 2001 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.031) unstable; urgency=low

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Wed, 24 Oct 2001 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.03) unstable; urgency=low

  * Now proxy can restrict remote IP, E.g. to enable use proxy only for
    local network.
  * ISAPI updated to most compatible with diferent DLLs.
  * Bug in SMTP fixed.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Fri, 21 Sep 2001 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.022) unstable; urgency=low

  * exceptions from external ISA DLLs are intercepted by server.
  * when requested file is absent, server adds .asi* suffix to file
    name and trys to find it.
    - It is cose to make redirect for moved files.
  * In previous version, path to web root directory couldn't content
    space. Fixed.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Mon, 03 Sep 2001 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.02) unstable; urgency=low

  * Now template character '*' is supported in default file name. You
    can direct default file name "index.*" and server may return
    "index.htm", or run "index.cgi" from cgi-bin, etc.
  * SMTP server was updated.
    - Now mail routing detects correctly. Just direct DNS server in
      SMTP options, to use this feature.
  * DNS server was updated.
    - If you would like to create your own dialup network, you can add
      last record "your_ip * " to DNS-hosts file, and all request to
      unknown hosts will be directed to your PC.
  * When script includes from SSI, QUERY_STRING transfers correctly.
  * Some other little changes.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Wed, 01 Aug 2001 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.01) unstable; urgency=low

  * Local administration dialog box.
  * Optimised.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Thu, 12 Jul 2001 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (3.00) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Administration & remote administration
  * Full detail statistics
  * FTP server
  * SMTP server
  * POP3 server
  * Proxy also uderstends ftp:// requests
  * List of files returns, when directory is requested and default file
    is absent
  * LAN gate is removed.
  * Now configuration doesn't build into .exe file. Now it's taken from
    http.cfg
  * Other little changes...

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Mon, 28 May 2001 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (2.04) unstable; urgency=low

  * Now, system predefined names (AUX,LPT1,PRN,etc.) are detected as
    bad request.
  * QUERY_STRING variable is visible for SSI.
  * Options ssihtm, nossihtm have been added.
    - Before SSI tags had been checked in .sht*,.sml*,.asp* files only.
      Now optional SSI could be checked in .htm* files too.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Sun, 10 Dec 2000 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (2.03) unstable; urgency=low

  * User's mime types.
  * cgi_ident=\cgi-bin\ is a part of URL for identification CGI.
    - By default it is "\cgi-bin\", but now you can define it by your
      own e.g. "\cgi-", "\local-bin\", "-bin\", ".cgi", etc.
  * now you can restrict number of simulate request from the same host.
  * Bug: Before some memory didn't become free when request without
    file specified name came and default file was absent. -- Fixed.
  * Protection. Server will work more steady when attacker sends out
    few "bad" requests.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Mon, 22 May 2000 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (2.00) unstable; urgency=low

  * With simple DNS server!
  * With HTTP proxy! Memory cache is up to 16 Mb.
  * With LAN gate: To make Internet access per Nowell Netware Server on
    any PC into Microsoft Network.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Sat, 22 Apr 2000 00:00:00 +0300

 smallsrv (1.216b) experimental; urgency=medium

  * This version support dynamic DNS from http://www.dns4ever.com
    - option "ddns=user_name;password;domain"
    - server will be connect to DNS4EVER evry 5 minut for validate your
      IP.
    - key noddns to no use dynamic DNS

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Sun, 19 Mar 2000 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (1.215) experimental; urgency=medium

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Fri, 10 Mar 2000 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (1.215b) experimental; urgency=medium

  * ASIS files support has been added.
    - Those files content HTTP header in the begining.
    - Such files are being used for redirect inbound requist to other
      site.
    - This file must begins with keyword "Status: " after this
      returning code and your header is going.
    - After header one line is empty, and data.

 -- Maksim Feoktistov <max@smallsrv.com>  Mon, 28 Feb 2000 00:00:00 +0300

smallsrv (1.214b) experimental; urgency=medium

  * option "noicon" not to add the icon into systrey (server's window
    always in back)
  * option "noshare" not to use share directory;.

